The paper deals with the construction of a decentralized traffic controller for a large group of mobile robots sharing a workspace, which requires self-organization and the ability to deal with incomplete information and unexpected situations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Robotics (cs.RO), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also uses the potential field approach, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG), further supporting these sub-categories as likely candidates.
